Rabid Dog Attacks 16 People In Tanzania 
A stray dog, believed to be rabid, have bitten sixteen people including
nine children in Bukoba of Kagera Region, Northern Tanzania, reports
reaching here said today.
Kagera Regional Medical Officer (RMO) Dr. Katende Kashaija said the
incident occurred on March 6 and 8.
The RMO said the injured had been in hospital for treatment and no
death had occurred so far.
Kashaija said there were enough vaccines.
Meanwhile, Kagera Regional Livestock Development Officer Dr. Onesmo
Swai said apart from Bukoba, rabies were also active in Karagwe
district, especially Isingiro ward.
Dr. Swai said his department was carrying out an intensive vaccination
campaign in Bukoba and Karagwe.
